        "setup": "In Tableau Cloud Manager, configure a unified access token (UAT), then mint a JWT and use it with the Tableau REST API `signin` method. Tableau documents UATs in [Unified Access Tokens](https://help.tableau.com/current/api/cloud-manager/en-us/docs/unified_access_tokens.html) and notes in [Signing In and Signing Out (Authentication)](https://help.tableau.com/current/api/rest_api/en-us/REST/rest_api_concepts_auth.htm) that UATs are an alternative Tableau Cloud sign-in method.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "tableau_credentials_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Tableau REST credentials token",
        "generateUrl": "https://help.tableau.com/current/api/rest_api/en-us/REST/rest_api_ref_authentication.htm",
        "setup": "Call Tableau REST API `POST /api/{api-version}/auth/signin` using one supported sign-in method—PAT, username/password, connected app JWT, or Tableau Cloud UAT JWT—to receive a temporary credentials token. Send that token on subsequent API requests in the `X-Tableau-Auth` header, as documented in [Signing In and Signing Out (Authentication)](https://help.tableau.com/current/api/rest_api/en-us/REST/rest_api_concepts_auth.htm).",
        "acquisition": "manual"
